+# React Native Screenshot Prevent - New Architecture Ready
+
+This package has been updated to support React Native's New Architecture (TurboModules and Fabric).
+
+## New Architecture Changes
+
+### Files Added/Modified
+
+1. **`src/NativeScreenshotPrevent.ts`** - TurboModule specification
+2. **`android/src/newarch/`** - New Architecture implementations
+3. **`android/src/oldarch/`** - Old Architecture implementations (backward compatibility)
+4. **`android/build.gradle`** - Updated with New Architecture support
+
+### Integration
+
+#### For New Architecture (RN 0.68+)
+
+1. Make sure your app has New Architecture enabled in `android/gradle.properties`:
+   ```properties
+   newArchEnabled=true
+   ```
+
+2. The package will automatically use the TurboModule implementation.
+
+#### For Old Architecture
+
+The package maintains full backward compatibility. No changes needed for existing integrations.
+
+### Package Registration
+
+#### New Architecture
+The package uses `ScreenshotPreventTurboPackage` which extends `TurboReactPackage`.
+
+#### Old Architecture  
+The package continues to use `RNScreenshotPreventPackage` which implements `ReactPackage`.
+
+### Developer Notes
+
+- The core functionality is shared between both architectures through static methods in `RNScreenshotPreventModule`
+- TurboModule provides better performance and type safety
+- The package automatically detects and uses the appropriate implementation at runtime
+
+## API
+
+The API remains unchanged. All existing methods work the same way:
+
+```javascript
+import ScreenshotPrevent from 'react-native-screenshot-prevent';
+
+// Enable/disable screenshot prevention
+ScreenshotPrevent.enabled(true);
+
+// Enable secure view with custom image
+ScreenshotPrevent.enableSecureView('https://example.com/image.png');
+
+// Disable secure view
+ScreenshotPrevent.disableSecureView();
+
+// Listen for screenshot events (iOS)
+const listener = ScreenshotPrevent.addListener((event) => {
+  console.log('Screenshot taken!', event);
+});
+```
+
+## Codegen
+
+The package includes proper codegen configuration in `package.json`:
+
+```json
+{
+  "codegenConfig": {
+    "name": "RNScreenshotPreventSpec",
+    "type": "modules",
+    "jsSrcsDir": "src",
+    "android": {
+      "javaPackageName": "com.killserver.screenshotprev"
+    }
+  }
+}
+```
+
+This enables automatic native code generation for the TurboModule interface.
